body:

* Fixes.

name: v2.5.0-beta
body:
* Fallback upstream monitor option is back for preventing VPN leaks. (#119)
* Android Netd Service is removed for Android 8.1 and lower due to AOSP bug.
* Fixes. (#113)

We highly recommend v2.1.x users to upgrade to this version and provide feedback.

name: v2.4.3-beta
body: Design updates and fixes for Android Q beta 3.

name: v2.4.0-beta
body:
* Support copy/paste/share via QR code for Wi-Fi configurations. (#92)
* Support editing system AP configuration for systemized installs.
* Support for Android Q beta 2:
  - Support "Disable power save" and "Low latency mode" for keeping Wi-Fi alive.
  - Support changing repeater configurations without using root. (#31)
  - Support setting operating frequency of repeater to 2.4/5.0 GHz band without specifying a specific channel.
  - Fix permission issues.
* Reset repeater configuration has been deprecated. Users on Android 9- can remove remembered groups from Wi-Fi Direct settings manually.

* You can now monitor system tethering interfaces, which can be useful for [Instant Tethering](https://www.androidcentral.com/how-use-instant-tethering-your-chromebook). (#26)
* A new network status monitor mode Poll with root has been added, which broken devices can (possibly) benefit from.
* Fallback DNS has been deprecated. This change should not impact anyone as its value should never be used under normal circumstances.
* Fixes. (#76)

UPDATE: Promoted to stable.
